{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":190,"text":"So infectious diseases, right?"},{"time":1720,"text":"Infectious diseases \nare still the main cause"},{"time":3870,"text":"of human suffering and death \naround the world."},{"time":6197,"text":"Every year, millions of people die\nof diseases such as T.B., malaria, HIV,"},{"time":11367,"text":"around the world \nand even in the United States."},{"time":13713,"text":"Every year, thousands of Americans\ndie of seasonal flu."}]},{"cues":[{"time":17319,"text":"Now of course, humans,\nwe are creative. Right?"},{"time":19474,"text":"We have come up with ways to protect\nourselves against these diseases."},{"time":22799,"text":"We have drugs and vaccines."},{"time":24104,"text":"And we're conscious --\nwe learn from our experiences"},{"time":27489,"text":"and come up with creative solutions."},{"time":29416,"text":"We used to think we're alone in this,\nbut now we know we're not."},{"time":32481,"text":"We're not the only medical doctors."},{"time":34300,"text":"Now we know that there's a lot of animals\nout there that can do it too."},{"time":37706,"text":"Most famous, perhaps, chimpanzees."},{"time":39330,"text":"Not so much different from us,"},{"time":40831,"text":"they can use plants\nto treat their intestinal parasites."},{"time":43696,"text":"But the last few decades have shown us\nthat other animals can do it too:"},{"time":47143,"text":"elephants, porcupines,\nsheep, goats, you name it."},{"time":50522,"text":"And even more interesting than that\nis that recent discoveries are telling us"},{"time":54161,"text":"that insects and other little animals with\nsmaller brains can use medication too."}]},{"cues":[{"time":59603,"text":"The problem with infectious diseases,\nas we all know,"},{"time":62132,"text":"is that pathogens continue to evolve,"},{"time":64081,"text":"and a lot of the drugs\nthat we have developed"},{"time":66317,"text":"are losing their efficacy."},{"time":67976,"text":"And therefore, there is this great need\nto find new ways to discover drugs"},{"time":72209,"text":"that we can use against our diseases."}]},{"cues":[{"time":74113,"text":"Now, I think that we\nshould look at these animals,"},{"time":76667,"text":"and we can learn from them\nhow to treat our own diseases."},{"time":80331,"text":"As a biologist, I have been studying\nmonarch butterflies for the last 10 years."},{"time":84631,"text":"Now, monarchs are extremely famous\nfor their spectacular migrations"},{"time":87999,"text":"from the U.S. and Canada\ndown to Mexico every year,"},{"time":91109,"text":"where millions of them come together,"},{"time":93129,"text":"but it's not why I started studying them."},{"time":95660,"text":"I study monarchs because they get sick."},{"time":98051,"text":"They get sick like you.\nThey get sick like me."},{"time":100513,"text":"And I think what they do\ncan tell us a lot about drugs"},{"time":103200,"text":"that we can develop for humans."}]},{"cues":[{"time":105412,"text":"Now, the parasites\nthat monarchs get infected with"},{"time":107847,"text":"are called ophryocystis elektroscirrha --\na mouthful."},{"time":111726,"text":"What they do is they produce spores,"},{"time":113492,"text":"millions of spores\non the outside of the butterfly"},{"time":115884,"text":"that are shown as little specks\nin between the scales of the butterfly."},{"time":119261,"text":"And this is really detrimental\nto the monarch."},{"time":121619,"text":"It shortens their lifespan,"},{"time":123267,"text":"it reduces their ability to fly,"},{"time":125372,"text":"it can even kill them\nbefore they're even adults."},{"time":127879,"text":"Very detrimental parasite."}]},{"cues":[{"time":129760,"text":"As part of my job, I spend a lot of time\nin the greenhouse growing plants,"},{"time":133916,"text":"and the reason for this is that monarchs\nare extremely picky eaters."},{"time":137469,"text":"They only eat milkweed as larvae."},{"time":139464,"text":"Luckily, there are several\nspecies of milkweed that they can use,"},{"time":142549,"text":"and all these milkweeds\nhave cardenolides in them."},{"time":144905,"text":"These are chemicals that are toxic."},{"time":146699,"text":"They're toxic to most animals,\nbut not to monarchs."},{"time":149094,"text":"In fact, monarchs\ncan take up the chemicals,"},{"time":151316,"text":"put it in their own bodies,\nand it makes them toxic"},{"time":153724,"text":"against their predators, such as birds."},{"time":156003,"text":"And what they do, then,\nis advertise this toxicity"},{"time":158377,"text":"through their beautiful\nwarning colorations"},{"time":160398,"text":"with this orange, black and white."}]},{"cues":[{"time":162476,"text":"So what I did during my job\nis grow plants in the greenhouse,"},{"time":166348,"text":"different ones, different milkweeds."},{"time":168094,"text":"Some were toxic, including\nthe tropical milkweed,"},{"time":170848,"text":"with very high concentrations\nof these cardenolides."},{"time":174137,"text":"And some were not toxic."},{"time":175315,"text":"And then I fed them to monarchs."},{"time":177635,"text":"Some of the monarchs were healthy.\nThey had no disease."},{"time":180258,"text":"But some of the monarchs were sick,"},{"time":182033,"text":"and what I found is that\nsome of these milkweeds are medicinal,"},{"time":185056,"text":"meaning they reduce the disease symptoms\nin the monarch butterflies,"},{"time":188293,"text":"meaning these monarchs can live longer\nwhen they are infected"},{"time":191410,"text":"when feeding on these medicinal plants."}]},{"cues":[{"time":193324,"text":"And when I found this, I had this idea,"},{"time":196035,"text":"and a lot of people said\nit was a crazy idea,"},{"time":198343,"text":"but I thought, \nwhat if monarchs can use this?"},{"time":200817,"text":"What if they can use these plants\nas their own form of medicine?"},{"time":203876,"text":"What if they can act as medical doctors?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":206828,"text":"So my team and I\nstarted doing experiments."},{"time":208854,"text":"In the first types of experiments,"},{"time":210655,"text":"we had caterpillars,\nand gave them a choice:"},{"time":212825,"text":"medicinal milkweed versus\nnon-medicinal milkweed."},{"time":215566,"text":"And then we measured how much they ate\nof each species over their lifetime."},{"time":219186,"text":"And the result, as so often \nin science, was boring:"},{"time":222200,"text":"Fifty percent of their food was medicinal.\nFifty percent was not."},{"time":226451,"text":"These caterpillars didn't do\nanything for their own welfare."}]},{"cues":[{"time":230611,"text":"So then we moved on to adult butterflies,"},{"time":232686,"text":"and we started asking the question"},{"time":234577,"text":"whether it's the mothers\nthat can medicate their offspring."},{"time":237735,"text":"Can the mothers lay their eggs\non medicinal milkweed"},{"time":240509,"text":"that will make their\nfuture offspring less sick?"},{"time":243708,"text":"We have done these experiments now\nover several years,"},{"time":246236,"text":"and always get the same results."},{"time":248024,"text":"What we do is we put\na monarch in a big cage,"},{"time":250186,"text":"a medicinal plant on one side,\na non-medicinal plant on the other side,"},{"time":253669,"text":"and then we measure the number of eggs\nthat the monarchs lay on each plant."},{"time":258245,"text":"And what we find when we do that\nis always the same."},{"time":261354,"text":"What we find is that the monarchs\nstrongly prefer the medicinal milkweed."},{"time":264947,"text":"In other words,\nwhat these females are doing"},{"time":267048,"text":"is they're laying 68 percent\nof their eggs in the medicinal milkweed."},{"time":270392,"text":"Intriguingly, what they do\nis they actually transmit the parasites"},{"time":274612,"text":"when they're laying the eggs."},{"time":276077,"text":"They cannot prevent this."},{"time":277512,"text":"They can also not medicate themselves."},{"time":279443,"text":"But what these experiments tell us"},{"time":281680,"text":"is that these monarchs, these mothers,\ncan lay their eggs on medicinal milkweed"},{"time":286509,"text":"that will make their\nfuture offspring less sick."}]},{"cues":[{"time":291058,"text":"Now, this is a really\nimportant discovery, I think,"},{"time":293581,"text":"not just because it tells us\nsomething cool about nature,"},{"time":296415,"text":"but also because it may tell us something\nmore about how we should find drugs."},{"time":300101,"text":"Now, these are animals that are very small"},{"time":302101,"text":"and we tend to think of them\nas very simple."},{"time":304200,"text":"They have tiny little brains,"},{"time":305757,"text":"yet they can do this\nvery sophisticated medication."},{"time":308811,"text":"Now, we know that even today,\nmost of our drugs"},{"time":311389,"text":"derive from natural products,\nincluding plants,"},{"time":314148,"text":"and in indigenous cultures,"},{"time":315760,"text":"traditional healers often look\nat animals to find new drugs."},{"time":318595,"text":"In this way, elephants have told us\nhow to treat stomach upset,"},{"time":322002,"text":"and porcupines have told people\nhow to treat bloody diarrhea."},{"time":325291,"text":"What I think is important, \nthough, is to move beyond"},{"time":327946,"text":"these large-brained mammals\nand give these guys more credit,"},{"time":331754,"text":"these simple animals, these insects\nthat we tend to think of"},{"time":334656,"text":"as very, very simple\nwith tiny little brains."},{"time":337905,"text":"The discovery that these animals\ncan also use medication"},{"time":341876,"text":"opens up completely new avenues,"},{"time":344355,"text":"and I think that maybe one day,\nwe will be treating human diseases"},{"time":349069,"text":"with drugs that were first\ndiscovered by butterflies,"},{"time":352178,"text":"and I think that is an amazing opportunity\nworth pursuing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":356153,"text":"Thank you so much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":358316,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}